.nf
.ft C
\- micro: "\eu00b5"
\- copyright: "\eu00A9"
\- A: "\ex41"
\- alpha: "\eu0251"
\- Alef: "\eu05d0"
.ft P
.fi
.sp
List of useable \fI\%Unicode characters\fP  will help you to identify correct numbers.
.sp
Python can also be used to discover the Unicode number for a character:
.sp
.nf
.ft C
repr(u"Text with wrong characters i need to figure out")
.ft P
.fi
